- Your marriage is history, anyway.
- Edie...

467
00:32:25,143 --> 00:32:26,804
It was nothing, really.

468
00:32:26,878 --> 00:32:29,438
Basically, we both
got plastered on eggnog

469
00:32:29,547 --> 00:32:33,210
and we found ourselves
standing under the mistletoe,

470
00:32:33,318 --> 00:32:36,082
and we were like,
"OK, so what do we do now?"

471
00:32:36,154 --> 00:32:40,090
So I smiled and he smiled

472
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:44,254
and then Karl reached over
and started feeling me up.

473
00:32:44,329 --> 00:32:46,991
- That's not how it happened.
- You're up.

474
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:49,192
This is... It's so silly. Susie...

475
00:32:49,334 --> 00:32:52,963
Ladies and gentlemen,
please welcome Susan Mayer.

476
00:33:04,615 --> 00:33:08,779
♪ Start spreading the news

477
00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:12,219
♪ I'm leaving today

478
00:33:12,290 --> 00:33:16,124
♪ I wanna be a part of it

479
00:33:16,227 --> 00:33:19,424
♪ New York, New York

480
00:33:19,530 --> 00:33:22,226
♪ These vagabond shoes...

481
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:24,996
You're an ass, you know that?
No, keep playing.

482
00:33:25,069 --> 00:33:27,367
♪ Are longing to stray

483
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:29,372
There's a word you know.

484
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:32,841
♪ And get around the heart of it

485
00:33:32,944 --> 00:33:36,903
♪ New York, New York

486
00:33:36,981 --> 00:33:38,380
♪ I wanna...

487
00:33:38,449 --> 00:33:41,282
...just tell you that the affair
was one thing.

488
00:33:41,352 --> 00:33:45,311
I forgave you because I thought
that you were in love with her,

489
00:33:45,390 --> 00:33:49,258
and now I find out you were
just groping people at parties!

490
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:52,091
♪ Top of the heap...

491
00:33:52,163 --> 00:33:55,462
Karl, don't you turn away from me.
Look at me!

492
00:33:55,566 --> 00:33:57,090
[Man] Uh-oh.

493
00:33:57,168 --> 00:34:01,537
During our marriage, how many
other women were you sticking it to?

494
00:34:01,639 --> 00:34:04,631
As God is my witness,
it will snow on the hills of hell

495
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:07,542
before I ever feel sorry for you again!

496
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:18,314
- # New York!
- [Piano chords]

497
00:34:21,025 --> 00:34:24,358
As the police interviewed
the residents of Wisteria Lane

498
00:34:24,429 --> 00:34:28,160
about the mysterious disappearance
of Martha Huber,

499
00:34:28,232 --> 00:34:31,963
my husband Paul reasoned
it would only be a matter of time

500
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:35,938
before their digging
would begin to yield answers.

501
00:34:57,662 --> 00:35:00,324
Since he knew
the police had no suspects...

502
00:35:02,867 --> 00:35:07,531
...he decided to point them
towards the most logical candidate.

503
00:35:11,709 --> 00:35:16,146
You se, if there's one thing
Paul understood about the suburbs,

504
00:35:16,214 --> 00:35:18,580
it was this:

505
00:35:18,683 --> 00:35:22,278
No one's ever more suspicious

506
00:35:22,353 --> 00:35:26,881
than a new neighbor
who's just moved in.

507
00:35:30,695 --> 00:35:34,358
- Parker's getting sniffly.
- Yeah, I noticed that too.

508
00:35:34,432 --> 00:35:36,730
I hope he's not
coming down with a cold.

509
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:42,637
He doesn't have a cough yet, but he has
this post nasal drip thing happening.

510
00:35:42,707 --> 00:35:45,005
I'll make an appointment for him.

511
00:35:45,109 --> 00:35:48,340
I always say
it is better to be safe than sorry.

512
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:52,643
Little kids get sick,
and it's, sorry, out of control.

513
00:35:56,087 --> 00:36:01,286
[Faint] And kids with these colds,
it's just a vicious cycle.

514
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:18,665
Um, Claire?

515
00:36:18,743 --> 00:36:20,040
[Rustling papers]

516
00:36:21,646 --> 00:36:24,581
We have to make some changes.

517
00:36:27,718 --> 00:36:29,379
[Andrew] What are you doing?

518
00:36:29,453 --> 00:36:32,820
Packing up your father's things
for when he moves out.

519
00:36:32,924 --> 00:36:35,415
Here, let me help you.

520
00:36:37,895 --> 00:36:40,762
Look, I talked to Dad,

521
00:36:40,831 --> 00:36:43,959
and it turns out
you were telling the truth.

522
00:36:46,704 --> 00:36:49,935
Andrew, I'm so sorry
that I said anything.

523
00:36:50,007 --> 00:36:53,807
No, I'm glad you did. Now I know.

524
00:36:53,911 --> 00:36:56,937
There comes this point
in every boy's life.

525
00:36:57,048 --> 00:37:00,017
What? Find out his dad's
screwing around?

526
00:37:00,818 --> 00:37:03,753
No. That his father's only human.

527
00:37:05,990 --> 00:37:08,049
So why are you taking care of him?

528
00:37:08,159 --> 00:37:11,993
Because of what Danielle and I said?
Because you can forget that.

529
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:14,691
- I'll help take his stuff out.
- That's sweet.

530
00:37:14,799 --> 00:37:18,565
But I'm taking care of him
because it's the right thing to do.

531
00:37:18,669 --> 00:37:21,297
Why are you being
such a pushover?

532
00:37:21,405 --> 00:37:24,568
I mean, he cheated on you. He's a jerk.

533
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:30,274
Andrew, you will not speak that way
about your father in front of me.

534
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:33,806
Why the hell not? I mean,
for once I'm actually on your side.

535
00:37:33,884 --> 00:37:36,978
Yes, I'm angry with him.
I am gonna divorce him.

536
00:37:37,054 --> 00:37:39,454
I may even marry somebody else,

537
00:37:39,523 --> 00:37:43,289
but your father is and always will be
the love of my life.

538
00:37:45,029 --> 00:37:48,760
He gave me
the best 18-year marriage that...

539
00:37:50,668 --> 00:37:52,727
...I could have ever hoped for.

540
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:59,407
And for that you will respect him.

541
00:37:59,477 --> 00:38:01,570
OK.

542
00:38:20,531 --> 00:38:24,558
- What is it? I'm really, really busy.
- I came by to apologize.

543
00:38:24,635 --> 00:38:29,868
Oh. Well, in that case, come on in.
I'm not doing anything.

544
00:38:33,277 --> 00:38:37,043
I can't believe
Edie brought the whole thing up.

545
00:38:37,148 --> 00:38:41,983
Susan, I am so sorry.
I... I thought I was done hurting you.

546
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:44,112
Yeah, me too.

547
00:38:45,623 --> 00:38:50,492
And just so you know,
I'm... sorry for flipping out.

548
00:38:50,594 --> 00:38:52,892
I shouldn't let you
get to me like that.

549
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,594
- What?
- I do still get to you, don't I?

550
00:38:58,669 --> 00:39:01,604
That's the difference
between the plumber and me.

551
00:39:01,706 --> 00:39:05,233
Don't get me wrong,
he's a good guy. I like him.

552
00:39:05,309 --> 00:39:08,506
But I'm betting you two
don't have what we had together.

553
00:39:08,612 --> 00:39:11,445
There was always a spark between us.

554
00:39:11,549 --> 00:39:13,346
A spark?

555
00:39:13,451 --> 00:39:17,512
Look, what I'm trying to say is
he must seem really safe after me.

556
00:39:17,621 --> 00:39:20,556
A moray eel would seem safe after you.

557
00:39:22,460 --> 00:39:27,693
That's what I'm talking about, that
great back and forth, joking around.

558
00:39:27,765 --> 00:39:31,098
We used to argue
and push each other's buttons.

559
00:39:31,168 --> 00:39:33,602
Newsflash: I hated all of that.

560
00:39:33,671 --> 00:39:37,971
Come on. You have to admit,
when it was good, it was the best.

561
00:39:38,943 --> 00:39:41,537
What are you saying?

562
00:39:41,612 --> 00:39:45,548
Let's give this another shot.

563
00:39:45,616 --> 00:39:48,744
- You want me back?
- Yeah.

564
00:39:48,819 --> 00:39:53,984
Yeah. I realize now
that you were the woman...

565
00:39:55,326 --> 00:39:58,295
...that was meant for me.

566
00:39:58,362 --> 00:40:00,455
Wow.

567
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:05,262
Just so we're clear,
so you want to move back in here

568
00:40:05,336 --> 00:40:09,739
and be faithful to me and love me
with all your heart and soul?

569
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:14,977
- Absolutely.
- Oh, my God, this is so wonderful.

570
00:40:15,045 --> 00:40:17,343
Yeah. I know, I know.

571
00:40:18,582 --> 00:40:22,382
- I wanna kiss you.
- Oh, God. No, Karl.

572
00:40:22,486 --> 00:40:26,217
No. What I meant by wonderful
is that I wondered inside

573
00:40:26,290 --> 00:40:30,420
if I still had feelings for you,
if deep down I still loved you.

574
00:40:30,494 --> 00:40:35,022
- And?
- And... [laughs] There's nothing there.

575
00:40:35,132 --> 00:40:40,001
- Come on, you've gotta feel something.
- Well, actually, I do. Yeah.

576
00:40:40,104 --> 00:40:44,165
Excuse me. Oh, boy! [laughs]

577
00:40:58,989 --> 00:41:02,720
- Susan.
- Mike, guess what? I love you.

578
00:41:02,827 --> 00:41:06,092
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

579
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:17,070
- Did I come at a bad time?
- They're just asking about Mrs. Huber.

580
00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:21,843
I love him.
You can write that in your little book.

581
00:41:25,416 --> 00:41:28,180
We are all searching for someone,

582
00:41:28,252 --> 00:41:33,815
that special person who will provide us
what's missing in our lives.

583
00:41:33,891 --> 00:41:36,121
Someone who can offer companionship.

584
00:41:36,227 --> 00:41:39,355
George? Hi, it's me, Bree.

585
00:41:40,631 --> 00:41:44,089
I was wondering,
are you free next Saturday?

586
00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:46,830
You are? Oh, that's wonderful.

587
00:41:46,904 --> 00:41:48,337
Or assistance.

588
00:41:48,472 --> 00:41:52,374
Hi, I understand
your agency handles nannies.

589
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:56,776
I need someone experienced
and preferably unattractive.

590
00:41:58,949 --> 00:42:00,416
Or security.

591
00:42:00,484 --> 00:42:03,612
Hi, honey. Did the lawyer
tell you the good news?

592
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:08,021
You're gonna make bail.
I found your passport.

593
00:42:08,092 --> 00:42:12,859
And sometimes, if we search very hard,
we can find someone who provides us...

594
00:42:12,930 --> 00:42:15,763
I just called to say hi,
and I love you.

595
00:42:15,833 --> 00:42:17,733
...with all thre.

596
00:42:17,835 --> 00:42:21,134
All right, all right. Enough already.

597
00:42:24,942 --> 00:42:28,378
Yes, we're all searching for someone.

598
00:42:28,445 --> 00:42:34,441
And if we can't find them,
we can only pray they find us.

599
00:42:34,518 --> 00:42:36,611
What you got, boy?

